SUMMARY:

 This document proposes to provide additional time for the public to comment on a proposal to supersede two airworthiness
directives that currently require the following on certain Beech Aircraft Corporation (Beech) 35 series airplanes:
Checking the ruddervator static balance and adjusting as appropriate; fabricating and installing airspeed limitation
placards; incorporating certain airspeed limitations into the airplane flight manual (AFM); and installing stabilizer
reinforcements. Several comments received on the original notice of proposed rulemaking (NPRM) requested additional
time to respond to the proposed action. This proposed action would incorporate and update the procedures and applicability
of both AD's into one document. The actions specified by the proposed AD are intended to prevent structural failure
of the V-tail, which could result in loss of control of the airplane. 



