As discussed in section 3 above, there are State-wide regulations that will also impact the emissions of PM-10
in the Lamar nonattainment area. These regulations include Colorado Regulation No. 4, which requires all wood stoves
sold after July 1, 1991 to meet the emission requirements of EPA's Standards of Performance for New Residential Wood
Heaters in 40 CFR 60.532(b), and Colorado Regulation No. 3, which requires construction permits for new or modified
stationary sources. EPA previously reviewed Colorado Regulations No. 3 and 4 at the time these regulations were approved
