Cost Savings Act (15 U.S.C. 2004) sets forth a procedure for judicial review of final rules establishing, amending
or revoking Federal average fuel economy standards. That section does not require submission of a petition for reconsideration
or other administrative proceedings before parties may file suit in court. 




